  "notes": "Crimean Tatar in the standard Latin alphabet (Turkish-style, official since 1997). Largely one-to-one letter→phoneme orthography. ⟨c⟩=/dʒ/, ⟨ç⟩=/tʃ/, ⟨ş⟩=/ʃ/, ⟨j⟩=/ʒ/, ⟨ğ⟩=/ɣ/, ⟨h⟩=/x/, ⟨ñ⟩=/ŋ/, ⟨q⟩=/q/, ⟨ı⟩=/ɯ/, ⟨ü⟩=/y/, ⟨ö⟩=/ø/. Vowel harmony operates but is fully reflected in spelling. A Cyrillic orthography is also in use; this spec covers the Latin norm only.",
